This paper proposes novel techniques for quantizing neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on deep learning algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes a weight quantization scheme that is based on statistical characteristics of the distribution of weights, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed techniques on a range of popular models and datasets, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture for Neural Networks).
